    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Dhokla is a soft and spongy Gujarati snack made from fermented gram flour batter. It's steamed, light, and served with tempered mustard seeds and green chilies.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>25 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup besan (gram flour)</li>
        <li>1 tbsp semolina (rava)</li>
        <li>1 tsp lemon juice</li>
        <li>1 tsp sugar</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp ENO fruit salt</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>3/4 cup water</li>
        <li>1 tsp mustard seeds</li>
        <li>2 green chilies (slit)</li>
        <li>1 tbsp oil</li>
        <li>Fresh coriander and grated coconut for garnish (optional)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>In a bowl, mix besan, semolina, turmeric, salt, sugar, lemon juice, and water to form a smooth batter.</li>
        <li>Add ENO and stir quickly. Pour into greased steaming dish immediately.</li>
        <li>Steam for 15‚Äì20 mins until a toothpick comes out clean. Let it cool.</li>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan, add mustard seeds and green chilies. Pour over the dhokla.</li>
        <li>Garnish with chopped coriander and coconut if desired.</li>
        <li>Cut into pieces and serve with green chutney.</li>
    </ol>
